Unfortunately, by keeping ByteKey around, Apache Beam will come up with yet another construct representing a ByteString similar to what is found in several other libraries which is why I was suggesting dropping it.

Creating a ByteBuffers class with static methods for comparison/toString makes sense (if one doesn't yet already exist in one of our many deps).

Alternatively, turning ByteKey into an interface will allow us to have various backing implementations and just use a wrapper type to prevent copies.
